    "description": {
      "content": "Supabase Edge Functions are globally distributed, server-side TypeScript functions powered by the Deno runtime. They are invoked via HTTP requests to a project-specific URL. Edge Functions can access the Supabase client libraries for interacting with the database, auth, and storage services. By default, they require a valid JWT in the authorization header, but this can be disabled per function. This specification documents the HTTP invocation interface for deployed Edge Functions.\n\nContact Support:\n Name: Supabase Support",
